                <h1>Understanding Deshaney v. Winnebago: A Landmark Child Welfare Case</h1>
                <p>Deshaney v. Winnebago County is a landmark Supreme Court case from 1989 addressing the duty of state agencies to protect children from abuse. The court ruled that the state did not have a constitutional duty to prevent harm to a child once he was in its custody, sparking ongoing debates about child welfare and government responsibility.</p>
